defaultOur response also draws on the experience 
defaultof 
defaultSHIFT (Sustainable Homes Index for Tomorrow)
default, our
default benchmarking and good practice network 
defaultwith a membership of
default over 60 housing associations.  Together these manage over one million homes with over two million residents. 
default&#xa0;
default1.4.
default&#xa0; 
defaultWe welcome the proposals to rationalise and simplify the confused approach to housing standards and reduce the volume of guidance.  We also welcome the intention to clarify the distinctive contribution of building regulations and planning policy/guidance.
default&#xa0;
default1.5.
default&#xa0; 
defaultWe believe that alongside this need for efficiency policy makers must maintain an awareness of the limits of market self-regulation and the unique position of government in the management of environmental risks. This concern was strongly stated in a 2010 review by the Innovation and Growth Team: 
default&#xa0;
default“Primary leadership needs to come from Government, because of the degree of market failure and because plans for carbon reduction must reach into every fibre of the built environment, at a scale that is far beyond the reach of anybody other than Government.”
default&#xa0;
default1.6.
default&#xa0; 
defaultWe have identified a number of important areas that the consultation and its accompanying impact assessment have failed to address.  These are 
defaultcovered
default in current standards and risk being lost.  Many contribute significantly to the achievement of important wider environmental, social and health outcomes.  
