default&#xa0;default3.1.
default&#xa0; 
defaultMore serious consideration of overheating is needed
default: 
defaultOverheating is acknowledged as a problem but the consultation does not offer serious consideration of this issue other than a proposal to keep it under review.
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
default3.2.
default&#xa0; 
defaultCuriously, the consultation states that “there are no standards or regulations that directly control overheating for thermal comfort”.
default&#xa0;
default Yet, building regulations state that there should be a low risk of overheating and that this can be demonstrated using the methodology described in appendix P of SAP. 
default&#xa0;
default3.3.
default&#xa0; 
defaultT
defaulthe
defaultse
default existing 
defaultrequirements are in-fact already in need of review as the existing methodology
default 
defaultuses
default historic summer temperatures as part of its assessment and not projected temperatures, which could significantly alter the risk assessment.
